---
description: Rules for contributing to counterpart-toolbox
alwaysApply: true
---


All scripts must be bash-compatible (no bash 4+ features like associative arrays on macOS).

Lib scripts (lib/*.sh) export functions only — no side effects on source.

Sync engine (lib/sync.sh) must remain idempotent: running twice produces identical output.

The managed block markers are `<!-- counterpart:managed:start -->` and `<!-- counterpart:managed:end -->`. Never change these strings.

When adding a new lib script, source it in yourcounterpart and add a shellcheck comment.

Plugins live in plugins/.agents/ — never hardcode rules directly in the main script.
